The paper deals with the complexity of approximating the size of stopping and trapping sets in Tanner graphs of linear block codes, specifically LDPC codes. This involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and possibly statistical inference (cs.SI) since the paper discusses methods for estimating the error-floor of LDPC codes.
